WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:44.127 --> 00:00:46.338 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN] You are to go
by the call sign "Lycoris".

00:00:46.421 --> 00:00:48.173 position:50% align:center
Do you understand that?

00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:49.841 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Lycoris?

00:00:49.924 --> 00:00:51.676 position:50% align:center
We'll need to converse with you.

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:54.304 position:50% align:center
One of the mission objectives
is to determine whether a voice

00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:57.349 position:50% align:center
transmission can be
received from outer space.

00:00:57.432 --> 00:01:00.477 position:50% align:center
So, we'll have you read
from what's written here.

00:01:02.145 --> 00:01:04.105 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Lycoris Cooking Show?

00:01:04.189 --> 00:01:06.775 position:50% align:center
Your physical state will
determine the script.

00:01:06.858 --> 00:01:09.110 position:50% align:center
If you have no health
issues in zero-G,

00:01:09.194 --> 00:01:11.446 position:50% align:center
read the recipe for borscht.

00:01:11.529 --> 00:01:14.616 position:50% align:center
If there's a problem, you'll
read the cheeseburger one.

00:01:15.992 --> 00:01:17.786 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
This wasn't in the mock launch.

00:01:17.869 --> 00:01:20.246 position:50% align:center
So why am I supposed
to read these?

00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:22.207 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
It's a secret code.

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:26.211 position:50% align:center
If the UK is able to intercept
your transmission somehow.

00:01:26.294 --> 00:01:28.338 position:50% align:center
Well, then I'm sure you
can see how that could

00:01:28.421 --> 00:01:30.924 position:50% align:center
be problematic for us.

00:01:31.007 --> 00:01:34.219 position:50% align:center
We speak plainly and they'll
suspect that we're sending

00:01:34.302 --> 00:01:36.680 position:50% align:center
a human into space in secret.

00:01:36.763 --> 00:01:38.306 position:50% align:center
But if they hear a
recipe reading,

00:01:38.390 --> 00:01:41.226 position:50% align:center
they'll just assume that it's
some sort of cooking program.

00:01:41.309 --> 00:01:43.895 position:50% align:center
I think I understand.

00:01:43.978 --> 00:01:47.023 position:50% align:center
Now, listen carefully.
After you're in the air,

00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:49.526 position:50% align:center
you mustn't say anything
but the recipe contents

00:01:49.609 --> 00:01:52.153 position:50% align:center
until communications
have been disconnected.

00:01:52.237 --> 00:01:55.573 position:50% align:center
And as for the explosives,
you saw them?

00:01:55.657 --> 00:01:58.201 position:50% align:center
Yes. Under the seat.

00:02:02.372 --> 00:02:05.625 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN] Don't do anything
unless instructed to.

00:02:05.709 --> 00:02:07.335 position:50% align:center
Is that clear?

00:02:32.652 --> 00:02:33.862 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:02:37.198 --> 00:02:38.700 position:50% align:center
Well, it won't be long now.

00:02:38.783 --> 00:02:41.202 position:50% align:center
[door opens]

00:02:45.623 --> 00:02:49.127 position:50% align:center
Wait, I know you... Natalia?

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:51.421 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:02:51.504 --> 00:02:56.509 position:50% align:center
♪

00:04:44.659 --> 00:04:45.744 position:50% align:center
[ANYA]
Here.

00:04:45.827 --> 00:04:47.203 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Thank you.

00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:49.330 position:50% align:center
[ENGINEER A] Hey! You can't
bring that onto the ship!

00:04:49.414 --> 00:04:51.541 position:50% align:center
[IRINA grunts]
Stop it!

00:04:54.627 --> 00:04:55.545 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:55.628 --> 00:04:57.380 position:50% align:center
[ENGINEER A gasps]
Hand it here!

00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:58.715 position:50% align:center
[footsteps]

00:04:58.798 --> 00:05:00.008 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Wait!

00:05:02.969 --> 00:05:04.179 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Lev!

00:05:06.848 --> 00:05:07.849 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
They made the whole incident

00:05:07.932 --> 00:05:10.018 position:50% align:center
the other day disappear.

00:05:10.101 --> 00:05:14.314 position:50% align:center
Turns out the centrifuge
wasn't broken, it was sabotaged.

00:05:14.397 --> 00:05:15.357 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
What?

00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:17.442 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
I was told the truth.

00:05:17.525 --> 00:05:20.278 position:50% align:center
Franz deliberately caused
the equipment failure.

00:05:20.362 --> 00:05:22.781 position:50% align:center
What? But why would he do that?

00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:24.491 position:50% align:center
He was acting on
orders from someone

00:05:24.574 --> 00:05:26.242 position:50% align:center
who opposes the Chief.

00:05:26.326 --> 00:05:28.370 position:50% align:center
If N-Forty-Four had been killed,

00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:30.413 position:50% align:center
then the project
would've failed.

00:05:30.497 --> 00:05:32.665 position:50% align:center
Which would mean a
demotion for the Chief.

00:05:32.749 --> 00:05:35.001 position:50% align:center
So what are they going
to do to Franz?

00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:38.463 position:50% align:center
I'm afraid no record of
such a person exists here.

00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:42.509 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
I don't believe it.

00:05:42.592 --> 00:05:44.969 position:50% align:center
That's the country we live in.

00:05:45.053 --> 00:05:48.056 position:50% align:center
Anyway. I'm glad I
can watch the launch.

00:05:48.139 --> 00:05:49.766 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Thanks for getting this back.

00:05:49.849 --> 00:05:54.020 position:50% align:center
I know you want to take it with
you, but leave it here with me.

00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:59.484 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] Okay, but if you ever
get a chance to go to the moon,

00:05:59.567 --> 00:06:01.403 position:50% align:center
promise me you'll take it.

00:06:03.613 --> 00:06:06.199 position:50% align:center
Sorry, but that's
not gonna happen.

00:06:08.118 --> 00:06:10.912 position:50% align:center
Oh. I see.

00:06:10.995 --> 00:06:13.415 position:50% align:center
Because you're the one who's
gonna be taking it there.

00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:14.791 position:50% align:center
[IRINA gasps]

00:06:14.874 --> 00:06:16.084 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Mm?

00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:20.505 position:50% align:center
What is it? Tell me.

00:06:22.048 --> 00:06:24.384 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Mm...

00:06:24.467 --> 00:06:26.011 position:50% align:center
That's what's missing!

00:06:29.723 --> 00:06:32.809 position:50% align:center
Now there's no way you'll
be mistaken for an enemy.

00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:38.898 position:50% align:center
We're departing for
the launch site!

00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:48.366 position:50% align:center
That's it, Irina.

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:59.044 position:50% align:center
I appreciate all
your hard work, Lev.

00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.003 position:50% align:center
Sir.

00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:02.589 position:50% align:center
Lycoris. Time to
enter the cabin.

00:07:02.672 --> 00:07:05.050 position:50% align:center
We'll do the final
checks and then launch.

00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:07.886 position:50% align:center
That's planned for
108 minutes from now.

00:07:07.969 --> 00:07:09.471 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Hm!

00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.973 position:50% align:center
You've become quite
a fine cosmonaut.

00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:14.142 position:50% align:center
That might have something
to do with my teacher.

00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:15.518 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Hm!

00:07:32.702 --> 00:07:35.705 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] I may never
see this planet again.

00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:38.041 position:50% align:center
Or Lev.

00:07:38.124 --> 00:07:41.086 position:50% align:center
No. I'll come back.

00:07:41.169 --> 00:07:42.545 position:50% align:center
I know it.

00:07:49.636 --> 00:07:54.015 position:50% align:center
Make no mistakes.
This mission is everything.

00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:56.351 position:50% align:center
Do not lose focus!

00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.270 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] Come in, Polnoc,
this is Lycoris.

00:07:59.354 --> 00:08:01.481 position:50% align:center
This is Polnoc, we can hear you.

00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:04.025 position:50% align:center
Communications testing complete.

00:08:04.109 --> 00:08:05.652 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
One hour until launch.

00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:08.613 position:50% align:center
We're almost finished
with the final tests.

00:08:08.697 --> 00:08:09.864 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Roger.

00:08:09.948 --> 00:08:11.783 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER B] The cabin
pressure appears normal.

00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:14.494 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Thirty minutes until launch.

00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:17.580 position:50% align:center
[MOZHAVSKY]
Heart rate: 64. Breathing: 24.

00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.416 position:50% align:center
No issues found.

00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:22.335 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Fifteen minutes until launch.

00:08:22.419 --> 00:08:25.296 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN] Lycoris, we're running
a little late here.

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:28.967 position:50% align:center
But don't worry, it's normal for
a launch to have some delays.

00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:30.301 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Roger.

00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:33.263 position:50% align:center
We'll ignite when the final
checks are complete.

00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:35.348 position:50% align:center
There won't be a countdown.

00:08:35.432 --> 00:08:38.852 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Yes, sir. Preparing for launch.

00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:40.687 position:50% align:center
Final checks, ready!

00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:42.605 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER C]
Range finder, go.

00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:44.399 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER B]
Comms system, go.

00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:46.735 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER D]
Propulsion, go.

00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:48.361 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
All systems, go!

00:08:48.445 --> 00:08:49.487 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Set keys!

00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.156 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Keys set!

00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:53.575 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Ignition!

00:08:56.494 --> 00:08:58.413 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Preliminary stage!

00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:03.126 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Intermediate stage!

00:09:06.338 --> 00:09:08.548 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Hold on tight, Lycoris.

00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:09.841 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Roger!

00:09:11.843 --> 00:09:13.470 position:50% align:center
Engine ignition!

00:09:13.553 --> 00:09:14.596 position:50% align:center
Combustion!

00:09:14.679 --> 00:09:16.014 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER B]
Engines firing.

00:09:19.184 --> 00:09:20.393 position:50% align:center
Now launch!

00:09:30.528 --> 00:09:32.906 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Irina. Good luck!

00:09:49.381 --> 00:09:51.383 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Oh, wow. She made it!

00:09:51.466 --> 00:09:52.759 position:50% align:center
Alright!

00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:55.345 position:50% align:center
[LAUNCH CREW gasps]

00:09:55.428 --> 00:09:58.640 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN] Silence! Now's the
time to concentrate!

00:09:59.933 --> 00:10:04.062 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Altitude: 4,000! 5,000!

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:05.980 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER D]
Tracking the rocket's path now.

00:10:06.064 --> 00:10:08.900 position:50% align:center
Position and acceleration
are looking good.

00:10:08.983 --> 00:10:11.111 position:50% align:center
Engine temp and pressure
are both normal.

00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:17.575 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:21.079 position:50% align:center
That doesn't mean the flight's
gone bad, but get it fixed!

00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:23.915 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER C]
First stage separation.

00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:28.128 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER B] Cabin temp
holding at 20 degrees.

00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:32.173 position:50% align:center
[ANYA gasps]
Heart rate is at 150!

00:10:32.257 --> 00:10:33.508 position:50% align:center
She's breathing too fast!

00:10:33.591 --> 00:10:34.592 position:50% align:center
This is serious!

00:10:34.676 --> 00:10:35.927 position:50% align:center
What?

00:10:36.011 --> 00:10:38.221 position:50% align:center
Not good. At this rate,
it'll lose consciousness.

00:10:38.304 --> 00:10:39.848 position:50% align:center
Give me the recipe!

00:10:39.931 --> 00:10:41.766 position:50% align:center
Lycoris, speak to us!

00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:44.769 position:50% align:center
This is Polnoc! Come in!

00:10:44.853 --> 00:10:48.023 position:50% align:center
No response.
Are we still connected?

00:10:48.106 --> 00:10:49.774 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER E]
We should be, sir.

00:10:49.858 --> 00:10:51.526 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
Lycoris, the recipe!

00:10:51.609 --> 00:10:53.570 position:50% align:center
Which is it? Come in!

00:10:53.653 --> 00:10:55.363 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Ninety-five thousand!

00:10:55.447 --> 00:10:57.699 position:50% align:center
What's happening? Lycoris!

00:10:57.782 --> 00:11:01.745 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
One hundred! One-hundred-one!

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:03.830 position:50% align:center
Altitude broke ten kilos.

00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:06.332 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER F]
Fairing jettison.

00:11:06.416 --> 00:11:08.501 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A] Flight is
maintaining its course.

00:11:09.502 --> 00:11:11.629 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER F]
Second stage jettison.

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:14.507 position:50% align:center
Third stage ignition.

00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:16.259 position:50% align:center
Get that picture feed going!

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:17.844 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER E]
Still investigating.

00:11:17.927 --> 00:11:20.263 position:50% align:center
Third stage burn
is now completed.

00:11:20.347 --> 00:11:22.307 position:50% align:center
And third stage jettison.

00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:25.602 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER C] Altitude stable,
we've reached orbital velocity.

00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:27.854 position:50% align:center
The launch was successful!

00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:34.152 position:50% align:center
Lycoris! Is it borscht,
or a cheeseburger?

00:11:34.235 --> 00:11:36.988 position:50% align:center
[VICE-PRESIDENT]
Did her brains get scrambled?

00:11:37.072 --> 00:11:38.365 position:50% align:center
Is she dead?

00:11:38.448 --> 00:11:41.117 position:50% align:center
[sniffs]
Oh, no...

00:11:52.962 --> 00:11:55.382 position:50% align:center
--[beeping]
--[CONTROLLER A, LEV] Huh?

00:11:57.342 --> 00:12:01.763 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Huh? I--What? Where?

00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.640 position:50% align:center
Lycoris! The reading!

00:12:03.723 --> 00:12:06.267 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Oh! Uh, right!

00:12:06.351 --> 00:12:09.062 position:50% align:center
Today's recipe is...

00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:10.480 position:50% align:center
...borscht!

00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:14.401 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:14.484 --> 00:12:16.569 position:50% align:center
Borscht! That's wonderful!

00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:18.029 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:12:18.113 --> 00:12:20.490 position:50% align:center
--[ANYA] Yay!
--[LAUNCH CREW cheer]

00:12:23.493 --> 00:12:28.498 position:50% align:center
♪

00:12:34.045 --> 00:12:38.008 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] Um, this is the
Lycoris Cooking Show!

00:12:38.091 --> 00:12:41.428 position:50% align:center
Step one: carefully peel
your carrots, potatoes,

00:12:41.511 --> 00:12:44.639 position:50% align:center
and beets and cut everything
into bite-size pieces.

00:12:44.723 --> 00:12:45.974 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Chop the cabbage,

00:12:46.057 --> 00:12:49.269 position:50% align:center
then peel and slice the
onion and dice the celery.

00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:52.731 position:50% align:center
Step two: heat a drizzle
of oil in a large stew pot

00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:54.649 position:50% align:center
and sauté the meat.

00:12:54.733 --> 00:12:57.986 position:50% align:center
Time to add the carrots,
celery, and a pinch of salt.

00:12:58.069 --> 00:13:01.948 position:50% align:center
Once they soften up, add water
and half of a quartered tomato.

00:13:03.450 --> 00:13:05.452 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Now put in bay leaves, consommé,

00:13:05.535 --> 00:13:08.955 position:50% align:center
and your preferred seasonings,
and let it simmer for an hour.

00:13:10.081 --> 00:13:12.542 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] Step three: put in
the rest of the vegetables

00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:15.003 position:50% align:center
and simmer for 20 minutes more.

00:13:15.086 --> 00:13:18.590 position:50% align:center
Be sure to keep the heat low
so the potatoes don't overcook.

00:13:26.056 --> 00:13:27.807 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] While the borscht
pot is simmering,

00:13:27.891 --> 00:13:29.809 position:50% align:center
prepare your sour cream.

00:13:29.893 --> 00:13:32.687 position:50% align:center
When that's done,
you can taste and plate.

00:13:34.147 --> 00:13:36.232 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Top with parsley if you prefer.

00:13:36.316 --> 00:13:39.069 position:50% align:center
And now you have
a perfect borscht!

00:13:39.152 --> 00:13:41.029 position:50% align:center
Enjoy in good health!

00:13:41.112 --> 00:13:42.822 position:50% align:center
[LAUNCH CREW chatter]

00:13:42.906 --> 00:13:46.409 position:50% align:center
We're alright so far,
but don't lose focus now!

00:13:46.493 --> 00:13:49.371 position:50% align:center
Re-entry can be
just as precarious!

00:13:56.378 --> 00:13:58.171 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
So beautiful.

00:13:59.673 --> 00:14:03.051 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
I did it. I made it into space.

00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:07.389 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Looking down on it like this...

00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:12.435 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] ...I can't even
share what I'm feeling

00:14:12.519 --> 00:14:14.145 position:50% align:center
with anyone else.

00:14:16.398 --> 00:14:18.233 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] I wish I could tell
Lev what it feels like

00:14:18.316 --> 00:14:24.030 position:50% align:center
to be weightless and how
beautiful the view is from here.

00:14:24.114 --> 00:14:26.157 position:50% align:center
[IRINA gasps]
A recipe!

00:14:27.492 --> 00:14:28.785 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
Next we have a special drink

00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:30.704 position:50% align:center
for you to pair
with your borscht!

00:14:30.787 --> 00:14:34.582 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN] Hm? A drink? But our
orders didn't mention that!

00:14:34.666 --> 00:14:35.875 position:50% align:center
[LAUNCH CREW murmur]

00:14:35.959 --> 00:14:37.669 position:50% align:center
[MINISTER OF DEFENCE]
Could it be a spy code?

00:14:37.752 --> 00:14:39.754 position:50% align:center
[VICE-PRESIDENT] Comrade Chief,
prepare to detonate.

00:14:39.838 --> 00:14:40.964 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:43.883 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] I happen to
enjoy oleaster nastoyka.

00:14:43.967 --> 00:14:45.760 position:50% align:center
[MINISTER OF DEFENCE]
Nastoyka? What?

00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:47.345 position:50% align:center
[LEV gasps]

00:14:48.847 --> 00:14:50.598 position:50% align:center
Nastoyka and borscht.

00:14:50.682 --> 00:14:53.435 position:50% align:center
Those are both famous
flavors of our motherland.

00:14:53.518 --> 00:14:54.728 position:50% align:center
I think it's safe.

00:14:54.811 --> 00:14:57.188 position:50% align:center
So she prefers
booze over blood?

00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:59.733 position:50% align:center
Sounds like your
vampire's a drunkard!

00:14:59.816 --> 00:15:00.900 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:15:00.984 --> 00:15:03.236 position:50% align:center
Begging for her life
by pandering to us?

00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:04.320 position:50% align:center
[MINISTER OF DEFENCE]
Huh?

00:15:04.404 --> 00:15:06.364 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
That's not what she's doing.

00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:09.325 position:50% align:center
Oleaster nastoyka is
something between us two.

00:15:09.409 --> 00:15:13.496 position:50% align:center
[IRINA] ...beverage for
the kids, too. we recommend...

00:15:13.580 --> 00:15:14.956 position:50% align:center
[IRINA, LEVI]
...lemon seltzer!

00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:20.045 position:50% align:center
[IRINA hums]

00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:27.844 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:15:38.188 --> 00:15:43.693 position:50% align:center
<i>Sinus Iridum. Lacus Somniorum.</i>

00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:48.365 position:50% align:center
<i>Palus Somni.</i>
<i>Oceanus Procellarum.</i>

00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:54.454 position:50% align:center
It's an impossible dream.
I'll never reach the moon.

00:16:13.431 --> 00:16:15.684 position:50% align:center
I don't wanna die.

00:16:29.489 --> 00:16:32.158 position:50% align:center
[IRINA gasps]
Training was worse than this!

00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:36.371 position:50% align:center
It's no use! We can't
get the comms back up!

00:16:36.454 --> 00:16:39.207 position:50% align:center
Why not? We're past
re-entry blackout now!

00:16:39.290 --> 00:16:42.502 position:50% align:center
The cable's cut!
There could be antenna damage!

00:16:42.585 --> 00:16:44.254 position:50% align:center
[KOROVIN]
What else is wrong?

00:16:44.337 --> 00:16:45.422 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A]
Temperature's rising,

00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:47.799 position:50% align:center
so the heat shield may
be flawed as well!

00:16:47.882 --> 00:16:50.051 position:50% align:center
It might burn or break apart!

00:16:52.846 --> 00:16:53.638 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:16:53.722 --> 00:16:55.015 position:50% align:center
Irina? Can you hear me?

00:16:55.098 --> 00:16:57.225 position:50% align:center
Stop! You're not authorized!

00:16:57.308 --> 00:16:58.268 position:50% align:center
Irina!

00:16:58.351 --> 00:17:00.395 position:50% align:center
Is the cabin falling
on our soil?

00:17:00.478 --> 00:17:01.855 position:50% align:center
If it doesn't, blow it up!

00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:04.024 position:50% align:center
It will! Don't worry!

00:17:04.107 --> 00:17:06.651 position:50% align:center
But retrofiring wasn't
quite perfect.

00:17:06.735 --> 00:17:08.445 position:50% align:center
It's a hundred
kilometers off course,

00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:09.988 position:50% align:center
so it'll be hard to locate it.

00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:12.824 position:50% align:center
Please, Chief! Allow me to
assist with the search!

00:17:12.907 --> 00:17:15.160 position:50% align:center
Heh. Absolutely.

00:17:15.243 --> 00:17:17.245 position:50% align:center
Viktor! Bring her back in!

00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:18.538 position:50% align:center
Sir!

00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:22.751 position:50% align:center
[CONTROLLER A] The landing area
is the hundred kilometers

00:17:22.834 --> 00:17:28.381 position:50% align:center
near latitude 51.6,
longitude 47.4.

00:17:28.465 --> 00:17:31.676 position:50% align:center
So far, N-Forty-Four's
status remains unknown,

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:33.762 position:50% align:center
and the search team
is struggling.

00:18:04.751 --> 00:18:05.960 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:20.975 --> 00:18:23.728 position:50% align:center
It looks like the
seat was ejected...

00:18:23.812 --> 00:18:26.564 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Then that must mean...!

00:18:28.566 --> 00:18:34.906 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Irina...! Irina...!

00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:45.125 position:50% align:center
[LEV] If I don't find her by
dark, her chances won't be good.

00:18:46.459 --> 00:18:47.669 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:52.841 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:19:11.443 --> 00:19:12.694 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:19:12.777 --> 00:19:15.238 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
I thought she was a vampire,

00:19:15.321 --> 00:19:18.241 position:50% align:center
but she's an ordinary girl.

00:19:18.324 --> 00:19:21.453 position:50% align:center
She hates people,
she's stubborn,

00:19:21.536 --> 00:19:23.872 position:50% align:center
and she gets upset
when you tease her.

00:19:28.376 --> 00:19:30.879 position:50% align:center
[LEV] At what point did
I start seeing her

00:19:30.962 --> 00:19:32.672 position:50% align:center
as a normal person?

00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:38.386 position:50% align:center
[LEV] This is the first-ever
manned spaceflight.

00:19:38.470 --> 00:19:39.846 position:50% align:center
Enjoy it.

00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:46.186 position:50% align:center
Be back soon.

00:19:56.321 --> 00:19:57.655 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
What's that?

00:20:10.794 --> 00:20:12.128 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:15.590 position:50% align:center
She's conscious, you say?

00:20:15.674 --> 00:20:17.634 position:50% align:center
Roger that! Well done!

00:20:17.717 --> 00:20:22.722 position:50% align:center
[LAUNCH CREW claps, cheers]

00:20:24.432 --> 00:20:27.727 position:50% align:center
Understood. Then we'll start
heading over there right away.

00:20:32.691 --> 00:20:35.276 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
I really... made it back.

00:20:36.486 --> 00:20:39.614 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
Yeah. All the way from space.

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:43.535 position:50% align:center
[LEV] Let's wait it out
till help gets here.

00:20:45.245 --> 00:20:46.454 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
You're bleeding.

00:20:46.538 --> 00:20:48.248 position:50% align:center
It's not a big deal.

00:20:48.331 --> 00:20:49.708 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
You're so stubborn.

00:20:49.791 --> 00:20:51.376 position:50% align:center
You're one to talk.

00:20:58.591 --> 00:21:01.428 position:50% align:center
[LEV] Your nastoyka
reached me loud and clear.

00:21:01.511 --> 00:21:03.096 position:50% align:center
[IRINA]
That's good.

00:21:11.646 --> 00:21:13.064 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:21:20.905 --> 00:21:22.115 position:50% align:center
[IRINA gasps]

00:21:23.408 --> 00:21:27.412 position:50% align:center
I'm... so glad you're safe.

00:21:27.495 --> 00:21:30.498 position:50% align:center
You're home, Irina.

00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:35.962 position:50% align:center
Thank you, Lev. Really.

00:21:38.006 --> 00:21:40.925 position:50% align:center
[LEV] No one in the future
will ever have any idea

00:21:41.009 --> 00:21:43.928 position:50% align:center
of what an incredible
thing Irina accomplished.

00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:47.724 position:50% align:center
[LEV] She won't receive
any praise for it,

00:21:47.807 --> 00:21:50.352 position:50% align:center
and her name won't
go down in history.

00:21:51.644 --> 00:21:54.898 position:50% align:center
[LEV]
In fact, it'll be the opposite.

00:21:54.981 --> 00:21:58.610 position:50% align:center
The record will be erased
as though she never lived.

00:21:58.693 --> 00:22:00.820 position:50% align:center
But I know the truth.

00:22:00.904 --> 00:22:03.531 position:50% align:center
That this brave young
girl was the world's

00:22:03.615 --> 00:22:06.409 position:50% align:center
very first cosmonaut.

00:22:06.493 --> 00:22:11.498 position:50% align:center
♪